This code will produce a graph with two nodes labeled "1" and "2", representing the locations. There are solid arrows between these nodes, indicating that the provider can install at either location at both time periods. The legend explains the meaning of the solid arcs and the provider installation points.

To compile this code, you need a LaTeX editor that supports the `tikz` and `graphdrawing` libraries. You can use tools like Overleaf or any other LaTeX editor of your choice.

